    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TACHOMETER SETTING AND SWITCH SETTING CHART</title>
        <para>The tachometer circuitry in the speedometer/tachometer unit housing computes revolutions per minute based
            on the revolutions of the engine flywheel. To set the DIP switches, the number of teeth on the flywheel must
            be known. This information is in the TACHOMETER SWITCH SETTING CHART (ACCORDING TO ENGINE MODEL).
        </para>
